				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: LDoN song lineup<a name="24084"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 26 04 12:14 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I think it would be miserable if all bards were cookie-cutters. That's the coolest part of being a bard, there's never any &quot;perfect&quot; way to do it.
<br />
I don't have as many issues running cantata during combat as I do with pure manasong. Any health regen acts as something of a damage mitigator, and with a side effect of a bit of mana regen, it's not so bad. Pure mana regen during combat seems silly to me.
<br />
That comes from what I've observed on my necro, if my pet is hasted and I'm oom, we collectively do higher DPS than when the pet is not hasted and I am FM and blast with every DoT/DD I have. For that reason, I place haste/STR buffs for melees way above any mana regen for casters. Also, because I know the people I'm grouping with and I know that my cleric is a genious at mana management, running manasong is a waste of time. If I were grouped with 5 wizards, my attitude might be a little different  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" /></span></td>
