			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: LDoN song lineup<a name="47037"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 19 04 7:28 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>This thread is great info for a Bardly one like my self who has been shamed into grouping in LDoN's instead of soloing... (See my &quot;so whend does it stop being so good?&quot; post. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
I am just kidding.  I have done much lower level grouping and I am really doing more LDoN's now.  I was just guessing on which songs to twist and what to have in my line up.  It seems I was pretty much on the money. 
<br />

<br />
As a 44th level Puller in the last few LDoNs - mele heavy group with cleric and ench, here is what I used:
<br />

<br />
1. Katta's Song of Sword Dancing  - DEX
<br />
2. McVaxius' Berserker Crescendo - HASTE / STR / AC
<br />
3. Psalm of Mystic Shielding - MR / HP / AC
<br />
4. Vilia's Verses of Celerity - HASTE / AGI / AC
<br />
5. Brusco's Boastful Bellow - DD 
<br />
6. Cantata of Soothing - HP / MANA
<br />
7. Kelin's Lugubrious Lament - LULL
<br />
8. Selo's Consonant Chain - SNARE
<br />

<br />
Here were my thoughts on why - please give me advice or correct me where I'm wrong. 
<br />

<br />
Mele heavy so during all fights I twisted the first 4 songs for HASTE / STR / DEX / AC / AGI .  This leads me to an important question.
<br />
          - Do our songs stack? Does the AC from the first 3 stack? Or, do our higher level songs cancel out the same effect of lower level songs?
<br />

<br />
More on the line up.  I did not mem a Mezz  song since the Ench had CC duty.  Was this a mistake? I suppose if my pulling was not sloppy , this was fine.
<br />

<br />
I mem'd snare to control runners and to use for pulling.. I mem'd a low level DD spell to use for pulling as well . I used the DD spell in situations where there was a crowd. I used a low level so as not to create too much AGGRO. This brings me to another question.
<br />
     - When we lull, how long does the lulled MoB stay lulled?  Say there are 4 MoBs in a room.  You want to pull just one.  I would go around and LULL 3 of them and then DD the MoB I wanted to pull..  I didn't use snare for fear that the first Lulled MoB would awaken before the SNARE-PULLED MoB got out of his AGGRO range and he would add.  Do we have time to LULL 3 MoBs and pull with SNARE? 
<br />

<br />
I switched between dual weilding and playing instruments and came to the conclusion that my added DPS ended fights sooner than the benefit derived from the instruments modifiers. On off fight times during the LDoNs, I sang my heart out replenishing HPs and Mana.
<br />

<br />
We were very successful and we cleared the entire dungeon for more XP. So I'm guessing this line up was effective.  But I am very open to suggestions and advice. So please feel free to comment.
<br />

<br />
Thanks as always.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
